values:
yo dude..im madd tired but i felt bad because i haven't updated since like 1963. so how's life been goin for you? sweet. so yea uhh for the past couple of weekends i've been going to mixers (devon prep, malvern prep, and st joes prep), basketball games, people's houses, etc. it's been going good. hmm ill guess ill tell you how things were this weekend..dont know why but hey itll do.

Friday-stared after with audro til the games and before them we walked with monica to mcdonalds. it was cute reminscing about last year's crew season haha good times. good times.  then i sat with a bunch of people during the jv boys game and then with martha, mer, brehm, max, alyssa and other people during the varsity. it was sweet although my ass started to hurt major.  after it audo, max and me went to  the mall for like an hour and saw some kids. audos mom picked us up and dropped me and max off at her house. then max's mom drove us to larristers and naters to chill..we watched that stupid "cinderella story" movie which everyone adores..but i dont see anything really good about it. i think its terribly dumb. max and larrister fell asleep while me and nater watched it and realized how dumb it was. then larrister drove us home around 130ish..

Saturday-went home from max's and slept. then hadda clean the house b/c people were coming over before semi. audo and i got ready here then me,audo, and gret went to max's for pix. her mom dropped us off here and tami, dayve, mark, tini, adam and dan came here for pix. we left for semi and i danced the night away! i looked madd cool in the shades and hat and dancing around with my buds! hahah i must say that probably was the best dance i've been to. i had a pretty damn good time. after it all of us with maxine and larrister went to max's to chill. audo fell asleep b/c she wasnt feeling well and we watched some beat movie that some dorkwad made us watch and then we chilled. everyone left basically by 3 and gret fell asleep..except for larry who we drove home around 4 o clock int he morning lol.

Sunday-we woke up at 9 b/c max had work but she made me call out for her and act like i was her. man the things i do. haha "hi jon..its maxine. i puked last night after the dance." hahahah god im good. i went to church and then picked up audo. later we went back to max's with abunch of kiddos for the game. we chilled, ate, beat people up, made fun of each other, etc. the commercials basically sucked. there wasnt any good ones except for the one budweiser or heinecken, the mustang was good the first time they played it oh and definitely the emerald nuts one with the unicorn, santa and easter bunny. unfortunately the eagles didnt win and didnt play so well..but yea.. me and audo came back here and went to sleep by like 1230. ugh then beat school.

well yea im out..i dont think you want me to write anymore and if you do, well then ur stupid b/c im not. and im really tired like no other. ill write again probably next monday or when im in a bad, annoying, pissed etc. mood. goodnight haha its 5oclock. later -jen

okay.. i really don't feel like writing about my weekend..i mean it was awesome i'm just really not in the mood. i'm so friggin drained. i hate it. i mean if you really care that much which i know you don't..just go to greta's lj. i mean we hung out so basically hers would be sorta like mine except for my whole blabbering entry the whole time and hers is sweet and simple.

yea so i was sick yesterday and on tuesday i didn't feel so well either. teetee said for the past 3 days i've been looking flushed..i thought i was too. i haven't been in the greatest of moods..i've been terribly out of it and now i'm mentally, physically and emotionally drained. i have major headaches/migraines, stomache hurts like no other, and i feel like im gonna puke all the time. (gross i know but o well). i feel terribly flushed and i'm pale (well duh already) but like im terribly red in the cheeks. i feel terrible and just like crap. i did sleep for 16 hours from tuesday-wednesday (1130-330) or however many hours that is..but i'd think i'd feel refreshed wouldnt you? wrong! i feel like shit! i mean i sorta have a lotta stress and shit going on i guess but i mean its not so terrible i mean i could usually deal with this shit.

today i was just in a bleh mood. i tried to appear happy b/c i hate when people ask me whats wrong. i feel like i shouldn't make them deal with what i have to or bring them into it. because i feel bad that they hafta listen to me complain sometimes. they shouldn't have to listen to me complain and whine when they have their own life to worry about. but tonight i just like i dunno.

anyway..i guess im sorta stressed because of my grampop. i mean as some of you know he got in a motorcycle accident on friday night. some dickhead piece of shit ran into him//ran him over and speed away. what a fucking asshole how the hell could you do that to someone? ughh! that pisses me off so much. that shows how screwed up this hellhole world is..well at least some parts of it. so yea thank god there was an off duty cop near by that saw it happened and the car. but yea my grampop didn't have a helmet or leather or w/e on because he was only taking a quick little stroll around town. as some of you know or don't most of my dad's side of the family lives in philly/roxborough and some he was on hm..ridge & umbria sorta i guess. but yea so the asshole drove away and my grampop was on a ventilator, with tubes, his arms with the first layer of the epidermis torn off, 3 broken ribs, and a punctured lung. he went to temple which is odd b/c his hospital is roxborough but they dont have an emergency unit there anymore or he would go to hahnemahn in center city because he went there for his pneumonia, and past surgeries and all. but he went to temple hospital in north philly (where my mom works) b/c i guess that's the only one with open area. yea but i found this out on my way home on crew practice b/c it happened at like 530 and we got out around then. my mom dropped me off at the house and met my dad, and my sister drove home from work although she was onlyt here for liek 5 minutes. but yea i basically broke down when i got home and my brother hugged me and started crying to..it felt like a kodak moment sorta..except for we both felt like shti and were crying and well yea.. that night i went out feeling like shit b/c if i stayed home i probably woulda done stupid shit or just been in the worse of moods.

i mean i guess he's okay now hes off the ventilator and all but he still has chest tubes, and he needs therapy. ..i guess going to church every sunday and praying does pay off...i mean wat are the odds of getting a hit and run with no helmet or leather and having absolutely nothing wrong with your brain or him not dying. i swear..my aunt debbie musta been watching over him. with his upper layer of epidermis torn off his arms, a punctured lung, and 3 broken rebs and chest problems i must say hes pretty damn lucky. and the funny thing is my pop pop says " i don't think my bikes so bad...i'll be riding that thing again soon! don't you worry!" i love him.

there's one thing i just don't understand. how can the world have so much assholes in it to fucking hit a 70 year old dude and drive away. its not like you can't notice hitting a fucking dude on a motorcycle. i hope they find the bastard and sew his ass (what im pissed and sad not a good mixed) because it could be considered attempted murder with all the other shit of hit and runs, speeding, etc.  but yea i basically useda live at my grams for 10 years when i lived in roxborough b/c i went there everyday after school and sat and watched tv with my pop pop. hah he always made me watch jaws, and his stupid fishing and hunting shows. but i loved every moment. he always had in stash swedish fish and gold fish for us. and we just sat together. i miss it.

well i mean i guess i should stop talking because he's alive and everything's gonna be okay they say but i mean ive been so drained, sick, tired, and just disgusted. i've been in the worst moods and today has just been horrible i guess. okay you really shouldn't have read my dull stupid time b/c there's about 100,000 people that died in the tsunami and they have families but no homes anymore. well i just felt like i could complain to my journal and know that i am don't have the worst off which i already know. i'm gonna stop complaining and go watch the news and think of how to change this screwed up world although nothing can change it. i can't imagine what those people who were affected by this calamity (nice vocab) felt...= /

sorry bout the long entry..i felt like complaining and writing although i shouldn't have

_*jen

ps. you don't have to comment or sympathize. just think of all those people who lost lives and others and homes... and do something about it..or try                     i know i'm gonna think of something somehow

Hey..i sorta haven't wrote in forever but sorry bout that. i'm not in the greatest of moods right now ((Sorta sad)) but hey it happens and its also about 230 in the morning but i cant sleep. my christmas was good..pleasant and nice. got mostly clothes, cds, mp3 players, etc. it was no fighting which was swell. but yea i dont really feel lik talking or remembering so ill start from monday though hah.

monday-went bowling with audro, kato, nater, larrister, and jerry and all. it was pretty interesting night lets just say that. hah although it was fun especially dancing with kato and doing the shuffle, breakdancing ((our turns//rolls hah)), egyptian, the CHOP and more! Crap happened but you gotta deal with it and then i slept over audros.

Tuesday-woke up and left for new brunswick for kellys with audro. we arrived and hung out with kelly and sara and watched mean girls. memorized the rap "ALL YOU SUCKA MCS AINT' GOT NOTHIN ON ME.." etc. haha and were stupid. later laura (my love pandamonkey) and my fellow farmer matt. he thinks me and aud hate him but he knows we kid. later we met up with a bunch of people at bennigans around seven. alyssa, emily, quinn, pete, fladge, chuck, jeff, tara, and billy all went ((i hope i didnt forget anyone b/ci love you all)). it was amazing how much fun i had man. it was so refreshing because it was drama free, silly, fun, and just sighs. lol spilling lemonade, doing a crossword, making weird faces and whistling to the random boys waiting for a table, being silly, taking pix, writing notes on a napkin to chuck with alyssa, and so much more. we went to see "meet the fockers" around 945 with mostly everyone except for a few who couldnt stay. it was pretty funny and i had a great time even though i dispise going to the movies. everyone was so happy and smiling around me..it was pretty friggin pleasant. after the movie was over we said our good byes and then sara, audo, and me slept at kellys and fell asleep around 3.

wednesday- woke up at 930 b/c we were suppose to go bowling but instead we went to the mall which was fun. i got a cd from hot topic and new perfume but i like it for my room rather than me but oh well. then kellys dad took us 4 girls to the rutgers university woman's basketball game. me and audros first college basketball game was fun! we won against teh number 8th team in the country whcih caused me and audro to think we are good luck. after it we went to WHITE CASTLE. audro and me were flipping out..i hugged it when i got to the door it was amazing to see one! i felt like harold and kumar longing for white castle! we took pictures outside and got souveneir boxes (we asked for extras ha). then we went to lauras for a huge sleepover with a bunch of us lovely girls (about 10-12 i think). it was fun playing hardcore taboo, nonstop ddr, having fun talks and taking pix, being silly and being in the banana man fanclub with laura and alyssa, talking from sex/horniness to going to life and college etc. we also started the chock fockers club with alyssa, sara, audo, laura and me. it was such a fun night//day. havent had a good sleepover like that in a pretty long time. i stayed up til about 6 in the morning.

thursday-we went home and gave hugs//said our goodbyes. got home around 4 i think and slept 5-9 and now i can't sleep. thas about it im talkin to nater and chuckeroo b/c they're basically the only two up.

i sometimes wish i lived up there in princeton area or new/north/east/south w/e brunswick because i love those kids. they are no drama, amazing, great, not annoying, interesting and friggin rock. i noticed how much i missed them and i learned so much more about them and the best time i've had in an extremely long time. hopefully i can see them over spring break b/c laura said she'll have a tent party...and we all know what that means. ::winks::  hah were' silly. i dont like being home or in kop very much but i guess ill have to deal with it. = /  im gonna miss em and i can't wait to get my pix developed. i miss you guys. ly

well im out..i have no idea what im doing for new years which is tomorrow and sorry about the long ass entry you don't gotta read it obviously lol. comment if you'd like. gnite. call if you wanna hang out on new years eve.
~*jen

So I haven't updated in a while..sorry o well.
I dont really have much to say I guess. Days go by, they are'nt horrible and mostly amusing and interesting but nothing to much to write about. although i did tell you i would write about my weekend. i know its thursday and the weekend was about 4 days ago but hey lets see what i can remember.

Friday-Went to the game and hung out with dayve and melissa during the jv. Me and Dayve announced the game.. "SBK passes it to the other SBK..can UM come back?!" hah then during the varsity i hung out with dayve, kato (Bourbon), and julie. after the game i helped audo get ready to go to mer/marthas party and then audos dad picked me, dayve, audie, kato and julie up and we drove there. it was fun being stupid with ali and dancing around. i just hung out danced around, won twister once =D, and was silly..woohoo! then i hadda leave at like 1030 unfortunately but my parents picked me up and nicole k met me at the firehouse to go up the mountains. we got there at like 1 and just went to bed b/c we were tired.

saturday-we woke up by my little cousin dan being loud and stupid but funny at 8 o clock. but i went back to sleep. later around 2, me,nicole, my sister (meghan), my sister's boyfriend (vince), and my mom went to the flea market up there and i gotta couple of presents for people. then we went to country junction (best place man!) and had a grand time. me and nicole were being stupid taking random pictures, buying presents, me screaming for santa and being silly, playing with the chinese stuff, and just messing around. when we drove home we met the rest of the kerper family that was at my mountain house (cousins and uncles) at dominic's (pizza place). we played in the arcade and just hung out. we later went home and my cousin and uncle made fun of the people in my yearbook. hah my cousin, heather, new a couple people who go to UM or useda go to carroll and she had fun time looking at them. nicole, heather, and me went for a walk at like 1 in the morning and it was dead cold and SNOWING! We just walked and it was pitch black andscary o well. then everyone went to sleep while me and nicole played rummy and texas hold em with my brothers girlfriend til 4 o clock in the morning..good times

sunday-woke up early unfortunately b/c we hadda get our xmas tree and go to jim thorpe. haha we first went out to eat and to jim thorpe. it was fun and me and nicole went shopping with vince and meggie poo. i got a crapload of xmas presents and me and nicole found the 3 skaters of the time. we named em too! they were following us haha and then when we came out of the train station they were right there..were like uhh?! but hey they were hot..so itll do! then we went to get our xmas tree and foudn the rest of the kerper family. haha me and nicole took silly pictures and crawled in the hay maze thing! it was cold but o well then we drove home and got home around 8.

yea that was my wkend. this weekend ill prolly go to the games on friday and saturday. then after the game on saturday i think were taking maxine out somwhere special for her bday! =D =X. well yea if you wanna hang out or w/e or go shopping etc. just call me

happy holidays. i'm not overly excited but hey christmas always makes me happy and calm. i love layin next to the fire or decorating the house and making cookies! hah

-*jen

okay here's a convo i had between dayve b/c im tired of hearing people who say high school sucks, their life sucks, boys suck, drama is all over, etc. shit like that. but i mean really guys think about it. hs is what you make of it not what others make for you of it. i know i might get some like commits saying oh yea youre just saying this b/c you have the perfect life or you complain sometimes or etc. okay no i don't have the perfect life but compared to many people in the world we have it alot better. and yes i do sometimes complain and i think people should complain and say they're feelings if they want to. i'm just trying to give advice b/c i hate how my friends are always sad and like always depressed and shit. i know its your lj's and your lives but i'm trying to help you guys out b/c you guys are my friends. so yea try to be brighter guys.  everyone's sadd sometimes but just remember what i'm saying in this convo. i mean yea everyone gets lonely sometimes and its natural for people to be sad sometimes..but all the time or most of the time cmonn... you guys deserve better than all this sadness.

orangesparkles88: i hate it so muchh jen
StillDreamin723: yea ..im sorta glad im not really overly attracted to anyone right now but see dayve u gotta remember this is only teenage yrswe have the rest of the life to live so try not to let this stuff get to you..if you look at it were still only considered kids
StillDreamin723: try not to let this shit get you down although u dont want it to and u dont try and let it..but this is high school its full of drama but forget about the drama. fuck the drama.
StillDreamin723: after hs..we have college and well all go our separate ways and all this hs drama will be behind us and it doesnt matter who got with who, or who fucked who, or who went out with who, or if he cheated on her.fuck the people that screw you over and dont let them get to you b/c its ur left and ur le tting them take advantage of you by letting it get to you.
StillDreamin723: thas why i dont care if i have a boyfriend im 15 yrs old and ihave the rest of my life to have all the bfs i want..a person is not gonna have one every second of their life and if they do theyre stupid...bfs cause drama. chix cause drama too.
StillDreamin723: live life b/c u only get to once. u only get 4 yrs of high school and were already half way done and its spose to be the best years of your life so live it up to be that
orangesparkles88: jen..i fucking love you.
StillDreamin723: go out. dance. party. sing. make a fool of yourself. be stupid. try out for what you can. do what you can. be in everything you want to be in. try your best. work hard. 
StillDreamin723: although college may be soon and comes quickly dont let that get to you either..this is high school .experiment with shit you want. adn do whatever the fuck you want.
StillDreamin72 3: people will remember you but some you might lose touch with.who cares if people dont like you. not everyone in the world does. so just love the people who love you and who cares about the ones you dont.
StillDreamin723: so about this goof be his friend although he may be an asshole it seems..but its high school have fun. u cant have fun if you let drama and boys run ur life..so run your own life. make your own chioces
StillDreamin723: okay i think im good...haha that felt nice =D
StillDreamin723: i was tired of seeing so manypeople's lj entries about how they think hs is stupid and boring and drama filled...well if u dont like it then do somethign about it. its ur fault ur not having fun not anyone elses. sheesh people loll
orangesparkles88: you are the best
StillDreamin723: dont think about the times in college b/c all the movies// tv shhows are bs. live hs people live it up!
StillDreamin723: thanks dayve.
StillDreamin723: i fucking love you too.
orangesparkles88: everything you just said..it completely clicked

well guys i hope it clicks for you too. i know i just babbled on to dayve so she said it clicked so i guess it wasnt to jibber jabber. so try and think of what i said. and stop being so negative all the time man. sometimes go for it its your life its your feelings and every single person is sad, lonely, depressed sometimes. but some peoples lj entries are always that way. so have guys have a good life..thank you


ill write about my weekend tomorrow. later guys ly.

-*jen

Hey dudes! Okay so nothing's really happen i guess important lately but today was a good day man lol. Today we had a 1/2 day b/c of Thanksgiving tomorrow. I'm going to my aunt's house with the whole kerp family lol. hopefully it'll be good and I'll probably just end up playing with my little 4 yr old cousin Dan and my 1 yr old cousin Taylor and my sister and Heather (16). Today I had school and well it was just shortened periods in which we did absolutely nothing. haha although it was pretty fun. One thing I must comment on: We watched some random ass movie in Science Fiction about how a meteor striked earth and these two people became magnetic.. I was like WTF mate?! and then in spanish we watched part of a spanish music video. hah Bourbon (katie) was gettin excited b/c she thought Mr. Watt was gettin happy and she's like "jen keep dancing!!!!!" haha. So after school, Audo, Max, Emma, and me drove to Angelo's and ate there. At 130 we drove over to CADCOM in Norristown b/c we were supposed to serve in a soup kitchen but it just all screwed up and we only stayed for like an hour and half and then Varga drove us back to Audos and we met Brehm's car there. hah It was funny reminiscing our NJSP weeks. hah And we had like six people on Audrey's one chair squished on it: me, Brehm, Max, Mer, Mart Mart, and Alyssa hah but we were still comfortable. Then after the meeting larry and nate picked me and Max up and we drove Emma home. We ended up staying at Emma's til like ehh 930ish i guess or 10. I don't really remember but we ordered food, sat around, and just talked and messed around. It was really interesting and fun. Oh yea then Dreweroo came at like 7 I think or something. Drew drove us back to Max's and sat on her new couch in her redone room. It's very lovely. We were just being stupid, and it was full of tickles, stupidity, crossdressing, barbie girl, techno music, dancing, and well stupidity and funniness. I must admit although it was an extremely odd day it was way interesting and fun if you think back on it!

 

I know I'm a little late but I'm doing that Fourteen Friends crap...yea i join trends/fads late.. what now bitches.

one]-Oh goodness. We've been together since well we were born ((that obviously gives it away but oh well)). Through skinned knees, being teased, friends problems, boy problems, and every other fault and problems kids and teenagers have, you've been there.  We pretended we were the spice girls, had fashion shows, played on my swingset, played at the corner church and just had so many childhood memories together. I really would not be anything of what I am today without you. So many memories in which we continue to live on and sleepovers. You're always there for me and though I moved away from you in Roxborough I know you're just a phone call away and you still visit me all the time. I love you to death and would do absolutely anything for you.  Although you anger me sometimes because of the decisions you make, we always get through things together.  You probably won't read this b/c you don't really have online or w/e but you'll see it some day and you know I love you.

[two] - Oh goodness. So ever since I moved in 5th grade we've been best friends. About 6 years later, we've had our stupid little fights for like a day but gave up because we love hanging out with each other and being with each other.  Florida, sleepovers every weekend basically, birthdays, football games, mall, movies, and just all the memories we've had..well yea I would never replace them for anything in the world. You're always there for me when I'm in a bad mood and you always  give me aplace to stay when i need it. No matter what we have fun with each other and I can trust you with all my heart. I love you and we've been through a lot with each other and I'm glad we have been together because I wouldn't be able to do it without you. Omg wait!! Look a dear! ::kisses:: hah

[three] - Oh my. Well where should i start? Although I didn't like you when I first met you, we soon became best friends.  Ever since 8th grade, you've been there for me nonstop and help me through everything. Although we get in petty fights over things like whether a teacher is hot or not ((and no he doesn't look like him)) and how you can predict who I think is hott ((Which I must admit you're very good at)), we always kid around ((as shown lol)) and have fun.  This summer we spent every weekend and every other day together.  The shore, camping, birthdays and Knoebel's ((im giving this way away but just not saying their name)) were amazing and man, I miss those places!  No matter what I'll always be there for you and I'll be there to lie to your sister so she can think I'm lindsey lohan, the chick from play, and a model. haha. You always give me great advice and help me out.. and I seriously do appreciate and love you!


[four] - Okay although she's not gonna read this b/c she's never on when I'm on, I'd still like to say her b/c obviously I love her with all my heart. From the first day I was born you were always there for me.  We always useda fight about stupid things and now we just fight about stealing each others clothes, cleaning, etc.  You are always there for me to talk to and help me out with advice.  I think you're one of the best ones out there and I love you. You take me to concerts, out to eat, places you go, to Roxborough, and do so much for me.  I know this is really corny and all since well yea, but you are one of my best friends. There's not memories to name b/c the only memory I can think of is my whole life. Every day you either call me or are here.  I love you and always will be here for you. ((if anyone knows who this is, you can just say it when you comment lol..its not hard at all))

[five] - Oh goodness gracious! Well if it is you! We've had our ups and downs but we always make up by either finding each other doing stupid things and just always being together.  We love traveling with each other and making each other look like dumbasses together.  Everything we do..we do together hah.  During spring,  on the bus to Philly we always cuddled together and were together especially peeing in the woods =X. I can trust you with anything and especially to be stupid with.  We've had the best of times in summer and have been best friends since hmm.. 7th or 6th grade i guess? With so many memories of sleepovers, climbing boulders, ringing bells, and just well being stupid I'll never forget you.  You always help me out and we never stop having fun with each other.  I love you so much!

[six] - Oh my! But it is you! Oh gosh you're always there online and everywhere to listen to my bullshit stories and give me advice.  No matter what you alway seem to help me and I always try to listen to you and you're stories. You're lovely and so is your mom and I know she loves me lol.  We've had a lotta fun on New Years, movies, and I love hanging out with you.  Although I have a really long name for you that's made up of guy names (Wow thats a majorly giving it away), you are a beautiful girl. No matter what you wear or do, you are gorgeous and I love you.  Never forget that.

[seven] - hah all I gotta say is SPICE GIRLS RELOADED ((and you know who you are)). We were best friends since the beginning of 7th or end of 6th but ever since then we haven't stopped ((except for 9th grade in which I never saw you and we had so much crap going on)).  hah We've done so much together especially  music videos, burning each others heads..well my head, playing spies, burying squassoms, dances, dancing, singing, buying slippers and hittin you on the head with them, semi, sleepovers, MICHAEL JACKSON, extremely long night talks, and just sooo much more. You know who you are and we always seem to be so stupid and dance together. That's just are thing you know dawg! haha We're gonna hafta make a vid soon and have tryouts!  hah I love you and gnite ::kisses::

[eight] - Oh myyyy.. Oh jeez the co-founder and other member of the Cookie Club and Band-Aid club is one in a million.  Although you may have violated my scarf on New Years and it is still being washed in England b/c you know they do the best wash and all I still figured ehh.. my scarf will forgive me for putting you on the Fourteen Friends.  You're one crazy kid and we always giggle.  You useda say I had a low self esteem and was always depressed but you helped me become more confident and happier! I love you so much for helping me and contininuing to do so.

[nine] - Hey whore. We've had a few good times together I must admit. I'm so glad I spent my last night of summer with you <3 and that madd hott yellow shirt guy. RAWR! I love working with you and being a dumbass and making fun of you. It's really fun, you should try it sometime. You always make me giggle and laugh and know how to cheer everyone up.  Although we're not in the same pornogym and we can't sing the backstreet boys together in nude swimming, we still keep in touch and sing to each other in our free time. haha love ya kiddo.


[ten] - O man well if it isnt Cheese! O gosh since...probably 7th grade we've had some good times starting in miss castellanos hmrm. Remember our names... i think i was umm Stu, Spencer and umm o crap I stink I forget!. hah You always make me laugh and I love how you don't care what others think of you and you tellt hem to screw themselves ..well okay sorta. I love playing cards with you in study hall i must admit and although you're house is haunted, i still love your room.  we've had alotta good memories together and continue to do so while screwing up and sewing things together that aren't even supposed to be sewed. I love you and you always listen to me and try to and give good advice. love ya man 

[eleven] - we don't really talk at all anymore since about 7th grade but I knew you since I lived in Roxborough. We've lost touch b/c its pretty hard to keep in contact and all. hey..
Well now since I actually feel like writing..well I don't really but I know if I don't do it now I never will, but anyway I'll tell you, you lucky person you, about the wonderful amazing week of Summer of Service. My week was June 27th to July 3rd! 

For all of you who doesn't know what summer of service/njsp ((new jersey service projects)), it is basically a group of about thirty kids from different schools/churches that stay at st. joseph's seminary in princeton, nj for a week and get split up into work groups and go to activity sites in which they help out the community.  I worked at TASK (Trenton Area Soup Kitchen) with Kelly, Tim, Matt, Emily and Tara with Mrs. Sanford as our counselor.  We woke up at 7 and had to go up to our dorms at 12 in which we didn't fall asleep at all right away (obviously lol). We worked from 9 to about 4ish and from then on you did activities like dodgeball, volleyball, badminton, ultimate frisbee, soccer, etc. or just hung out. There was no form of media (radio, tv, etc.) for a week which I didn't even notice because there was always stuff to do but yea.  Every 31 of us bonded so well it was amazing and unbelievable and the counselors rocked! It was great to see Varga!
